# Data layer — Sequelize + Audit (MySQL)

- Models use `sequelize-typescript` decorators (`@Table`, `@Column`, `@ForeignKey`).
- Primary keys: UUID v4 stored as `CHAR(36)`. Timestamps in UTC. Soft-delete via
  `deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL` (`paranoid: true`).
- JSON fields use MySQL `JSON` type (blueprint says JSONB → map to JSON here).
- Every business table is auditable. Implement audit centrally via Sequelize hooks
  (`afterCreate`, `afterUpdate`, `afterDestroy`) or a global interceptor that writes to
  `audit_log` `{tabla, registro_id, accion, campo_modificado, valor_anterior, valor_nuevo,
  usuario_id, ip_address, timestamp}`. Never write audit rows by hand in services.
- Schema changes only through migrations; never `sync({force})` outside local dev seeds.
- Indexes: add for every FK and for fields filtered in list endpoints (estado, segmento,
  responsable_id, fechas). Enforce uniqueness on consecutivos.
- Reconcile blueprint enums before generating models (unify `segmento`:
  Gobierno|D&S|ProyectosEspeciales|B2B). Keep one canonical enum per concept.
